UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2225
1 AN ACT relating to child support.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 15.808 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) (a) By applying for Title IV-D services or accepting public assistance for or on
5 behalf of a needy dependent child, the recipient shall be deemed to have made
6 an assignment to the office of the right to any child support or maintenance
7 owed up to the amount of public assistance paid by the Office of the Attorney
8 General to the recipient.
9 (b) Notwithstanding paragraph (a) of this subsection, to the extent funds are
10 available, the first one hundred dollars ($100) of child support collected per
11 month for one (1) child or the first two hundred dollars ($200) of child
12 support collected per month for two (2) or more children shall:
13 1. Pass through to the recipient; and
14 2. Not be considered income for the purpose of determining eligibility
15 for, or the recipient monthly benefit amount of, public assistance
16 under Title IV-A of the Social Security Act.
17 (c) The office shall be subrogated to the right of the child or the person having
18 custody to collect and receive all child support payments and to initiate any
19 support action existing under the laws of this state.
20 (2) The Office of the Attorney General shall distribute all child support payments and
21 assigned arrearages as required by 42 U.S.C. sec. 651 et seq.
22 (3) When Title IV-D services on behalf of a dependent child are terminated, current
23 and past due court-ordered or administratively determined child support owed the
24 child shall be payable to the physical custodian of the dependent child for the period
25 of time the dependent child was in the physical custody of that custodian.
